    <h2>What It Means to Be 6'0" — Context &amp; Perspective</h2>
    <p>A woman at 6'0" is <strong>taller than average</strong> — approximately the top 10% of global adult females by height. Understanding where your height falls globally helps set realistic expectations about what a healthy body looks and feels like.</p>
    <p>At a mid-range healthy BMI of 21.7, a woman at 6'0" would weigh approximately <strong>72.7 kg (160 lb)</strong> — a useful reference point for understanding the scale of the healthy range.</p>

    <h2>Estimated Daily Calorie Needs at a Healthy Weight</h2>
    <p>Estimated daily calorie needs for a 30-year-old woman at 6'0" and mid-range healthy weight of 72.7 kg (Mifflin-St Jeor equation):</p>
    <table>
      <thead><tr><th>Activity Level</th><th>Calories / Day</th><th>Typical Profile</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Sedentary</td><td><strong>1872 kcal</strong></td><td>Desk job, little or no exercise</td></tr>
        <tr class="highlight-row"><td>Lightly active</td><td><strong>2145 kcal</strong></td><td>Light exercise 1–3 days/week</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Moderately active</td><td><strong>2418 kcal</strong></td><td>Moderate exercise 3–5 days/week</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p style="font-size:.85rem;color:var(--ink3);margin-top:8px;">Use our <a href="calorie-calculator.html">Calorie Calculator</a> for a personalised estimate based on your exact stats.</p>

    <h2>Health Tip for 6'0" Women: Taller frames carry weight differently</h2>
    <p>Taller women often carry weight more evenly. Pay attention to waist-to-height ratio (aim below 0.5) as a complementary metric — use our <a href="waist-to-height-ratio.html">Waist-to-Height Ratio Calculator</a>.</p>
